// closure_capture.fuse — W12-P03-T01 proof.
//
// Demonstrates an immediately-invoked closure. The W05-vintage
// single-statement-body spine cannot yet bind a closure to a
// local, so the W12 proof uses the inlined form: the closure is
// defined and called in one expression, and the lowerer inlines
// the body.
//
// A closure with no captures auto-implements Fn + FnMut + FnOnce
// (see `compiler/check/callable.go`), so this fixture also
// exercises the callable-trait classification for the simplest
// case. Richer end-to-end proofs arrive when the spine lifts
// multi-statement bodies and MIR consolidation lands env-struct
// + lifted-fn emission.
//
// Expected exit code: 42.
fn main() -> I32 {
    return (fn() -> I32 { return 42; })();
}
